text.value:
 Here is code to generate 200 div elements:

```js
const divs = [];

for (let i = 0; i < 200; i++) {
  const div = document.createElement('div');
  div.textContent = `Div ${i}`;
  divs.push(div);
}

divs.forEach(div => {
  document.body.appendChild(div); 
});
```

This uses a for loop to create 200 div elements, gives each one a text content of "Div {index}", pushes them into an array, and then appends each one to the document body.

You can modify this to add ids, classes, styles, or other attributes to the divs as needed.
